          "type": "ai_gen_block_46f1420",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "DER BERLINER SALON",
            "description": "<p>For the third time, Marie-Louise Müller was invited to present within the curated framework of <strong>Der Berliner Salon<\/strong> during Berlin Fashion Week. Set against the crimson walls and Old Master paintings of the <strong>Gemäldegalerie<\/strong>, the exhibition created a quiet but powerful dialogue between historic art and contemporary radical craftsmanship.<\/p><p>We presented two key looks from the new collection, <strong>Frost Fables<\/strong>—a concise edit of seven looks presented as capsule moral conclusions in line with slow fashion core values.<\/p><p>The installation centered on the <strong>Goat Dress<\/strong>, a full-length silhouette in white ÖKOTEX certified cotton that demanded 360 hours of traditional filet crochet to achieve its intricate openwork structure. Beside it stood the <strong>Ruffle Coat<\/strong>, a 400-hour commitment to dimensional texture in natural beige Sheep Merino Wool. Together, these pieces—representing over 760 hours of handwork—stood in sharp, sculptural contrast to the painted narratives behind them.<\/p><p>For closer details of the textures and more behind-the-scenes moments from the gallery, please visit our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/marielouise.mueller\/\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram<\/a>.<\/p><p><strong>Official Website: <\/strong>https:\/\/www.derberlinersalon.de\/<strong><br\/>Location:<\/strong> Gemäldegalerie, Berlin<br\/><strong>Context:<\/strong> Der Berliner Salon, Berlin Fashion Week<br\/><\/p>",
